{
  "text": "There is increasing data with regard to biological therapies, such as anti TNF alpha therapies such as infliximab (IFX), a chimeric immunoglobulin G (IgG) human (75%)/ murine (25%) administered by intravenous infusion and adalimumab (ADA) a self-injected, fully humanized recombinant monoclonal antibody (mAb). Reports state that they may be more effective than the placebo in the reduction of postoperative recurrence [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Despite this fact, one recent study has shown that IFX has the same effectiveness as azathioprine in reducing endoscopic and clinical recurrence [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "8414182",
